  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      All the preoperative biopsies of patients suffering colorectal cancer (CRC) will be
      immunohistochemically stained with a pancytokeratin marker to detect Tumor buds. then, the
      intratumoral buds (ITB) in the densest Region of Tumor buds, namely the &quot;hot spot&quot; will be
      counted. Subsequently, the probability of N stage (lymphnodes), M stage (metastases) and
      disease free survival (DFS) will be calculated based on an existing logistic Regression model
      already developed by our previous retrospective work. Additionally, a Standardisation of ITB
      using a well- established Software will develop an algorithm which will help to eliminate
      inter- observer variability of Tumor budding Counts.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
